@COKESTUDIOINDIA, also want to hear compositions from Tapas Relia, Ismail Darbar, Sandesh Shandilya, Monty sharma, Salim Suleiman(they have great patience in compositions which creates magic ,that we miss in most now). Also, want to hear Mohit Chauhan, Nikhil Dsouza, Neeraj Sridhar, Kunal Ganjawala people again❤💟. PLEASE BRING THEM BACK IN OUR LIVES AGAIN THROUGH THIS PLATFORM, miss them like hell.🤞🤞😭💝

snippet.textDisplay:
“Wanwun” definitely gives goosebumps!! Very well orchestrated 
But the main issue with the rest of the song is that the band ( besides the two male singers) don’t portray  the emotions as per the lyrics!! 
“Kya Kare kore moul” is a very sentimental line and should be corroborated  by the band in the most empathetic way.. even in rock version! The least you want to do it is to laugh/smile during that line.. the guy on the drums is enjoying it ( laughing ) and I m sure he probably doesn’t understand what it means!
